



Sr
Harlem [N.Y.] Sepr 28th 1775



This just serves to inform your Excellency that I returnd to this place from Long Island immediately upon the receipt of your favour of the 2d Instant& that in pursuance of an Order from the Continental Congress I shall this afternoon embark with all the Troops under my command for Albany there to wait the Orders of General Scuyler.1 I am Sr in haste your Excellencys most obedt hble Servt

Davd Wooster

